==English==

===verb===
'''nihilate'''
# That by which consciousness exists
# To encase in a shell of non-being
# Consciousness exists as consciousness by making a nothingness (nihilate) arise between it and the object of which it is consciousness. 

===Word Origin===
This word was created by Jean-Paul Sartre in the original fresh as [[neantir]. This was translated to English as '''nihilate''' by Hazel E. Barnes in the 1984 version of ''Being and Nothingness'', but was first used in English by Helmut Kuhn in his ''Encounter with Nothingness''.